---
description: Require shadcn/ui and Tailwind CSS for all DocVault frontend UI
globs: apps/web/**/*.{ts,tsx,css}
alwaysApply: false
---

# Frontend UI Standard

- Build every interface in `apps/web` with Tailwind CSS utilities.
- Use existing shadcn/ui components from `src/components/ui` for buttons,
  inputs, cards, dialogs, selects, alerts, badges, avatars, menus, and similar
  primitives.
- Add missing primitives through the shadcn CLI instead of creating competing
  base components.
- Compose product-specific components from shadcn primitives; do not copy their
  implementation into feature files.
- Keep colors, radius, borders, and dark mode based on the CSS variables in
  `src/app/globals.css`.
- Do not introduce another component library or CSS-in-JS framework.
- Plain semantic HTML is acceptable for layout and content when no shadcn
  primitive is needed, styled with Tailwind classes.
